ry** files. Since we operate in a stateless environment, these files are my only memory of our past decisions, blockers, and progress.\\n\\n### **1. What I Heard**\\nYou are asking about the procedure, timing, and format for updating the session files that govern our working memory.\\n\\n### **2. Recommended Next Step**\\nI handle the mechanics of updating the session file using the `write_session_memory` tool. You can trigger an update at any time by saying \\\"Save that,\\\" \\\"Note that down,\\\" or \\\"Update the session memory.\\\" I also perform updates automatically at key milestones.\\n\\n### **3. How Updates Work**\\n\\nI follow the **SESSION_UPDATE_SKILL** workflow, which dictates:\\n\\n*   **When I update:**\\n    *   **Milestones:** When a task or deliverable (like an `APP_BRIEF`) is finalized.\\n    *   **Decisions:** When you approve or reject an architectural proposal.\\n    *   **Blockers:** When we hit a wall or identify a major open question.\\n    *   **Directives:** When you explicitly tell me to \\\"remember\\\" something.\\n    *   **Session End:** I always write a `SESSION_END` summary before we finish a conversation.\\n*   **The Format I use:**\\n    Each entry is time-stamped and categorized (e.g., `DECISION`, `TASK_COMPLETE`, `BLOCKER`) with clear sections for **Context**, **Action**, **Outcome**, and **Next Steps**.\\n\\n### **4. Risks / Red Flags**\\n*   **Under-logging:** If we don't record a decision now, I will start the next conversation with a \\\"memory gap,\\\" potentially forcing you to repeat yourself.\\n*   **Noise:** I avoid dumping raw code or logs into the session file; I only record the *outcome* and the *location* of the work.\\n\\n### **5. Action Checklist**\\n*   [x] **Restore Context:** I have already read the last 7 days of memory (we are currently in a fresh state for this project as of today, 2026-04-14).\\n*   [ ] **Identify Progress:** Once we make our first architectural decision or define a scope item, I will record it.\\n*   [ ] **Handover:** At the end of this conversation, I'll provide a `SESSION_END` summary to bridge into our next session.\\n\\n**Current State:** \\nWe are at the beginning of the project. I have initialized today's session. No active `APP_BRIEF` or project scope is currently locked in memory. \\n\\n**How would you like to proceed? We can start by establishing a baseline for a new project or reviewing any existing materials you have.**\"}],\"role\":null},\"intermediate_data\":{\"tool_uses\":[{\"id\":\"adk-01c1af91-1054-4a4e-b3b6-d78343c556ca\",\"args\":{\"skill_name\":\"SESSION_MEMORY_SKILL\"},\"name\":\"invoke_skill\"},{\"id\":\"adk-325652ba-cf84-4ad5-8bdb-141071c667ed\",\"args\":{\"skill_name\":\"SESSION_UPDATE_SKILL\"},\"name\":\"invoke_skill\"},{\"id\":\"adk-a6c3071d-a655-4cc9-ad15-624efb23918b\",\"args\":{\"days\":7},\"name\":\"read_session_memory\"}],\"intermediate_responses\":[]},\"creation_timestamp\":1776141093.321756},\"eval_metric_results\":[{\"metric_name\":\"tool_trajectory_avg_score\",\"threshold\":1.0,\"judge_model_options\":null,\"score\":0.0,\"eval_status\":2},{\"metric_name\":\"response_match_score\",\"threshold\":0.7,\"judge_model_options\":null,\"score\":0.20842572062084255,\"eval_status\":2}]}],\"session_id\":\"___eval___session___1e6be0c6-7036-4062-95be-fa411fd0bb2d\",\"session_details\":{\"id\":\"___eval___session___1e6be0c6-7036-4062-95be-fa411fd0bb2d\",\"app_name\":\"architect_agent\",\"user_id\":\"user\",\"state\":{\"_run_start_time\":1776154249.9352202},\"events\":[{\"content\":{\"parts\":[{\"video_metadata\":null,\"thought\":null,\"inline_data\":null,\"file_data\":null,\"thought_signature\":null,\"code_execution_result\":null,\"executable_code\":null,\"function_call\":null,\"function_response\":null,\"text\":\"How should I update the session file?\"}],\"role\":\"user\"},\"grounding_metadata\":null,\"partial\":null,\"turn_complete\":null,\"finish_reason\":null,\"error_code\":null,\"error_message\":null,\"interrupted\":null,\"c